{"lemma":"رِجِيمُ","slug":"رِجِيمُ","root":"NTWS","root_slug":"NTWS","root_link":"/words/roots/NTWS","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"رِجِيمُ","root":"رجم","pos":"N","occurrence_count":6},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n14981"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1%D9%90%D8%AC%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%85%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"stoned"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"expelled; outcast; cursed","examples":[{"text":"الشَّيْطَان الرَّجِيم ― aš-šayṭān ar-rajīm (literally, “Satan the accursed”)"},{"text":"قَالَ فَٱخْرُجْ مِنْهَا فَإِنَّكَ رَجِيمٌ"}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the verb رَجَمَ (rajama, “to stone”). Words on this pattern, فَعِيل (CaCīC), often behave as if passive participles."},"ipa":["/ra.d͡ʒiːm/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n14981","headword_ar":"رَجِيمٌ","root":"rjm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marojuwmN","text_ar":"مَرْجُومٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thrown at,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cast at,"},{"kind":"text","text":"with stones. (S.) The former is said to be applied to the devil because he is cast at ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mrjwm","text_ar":"مرجوم"},{"kind":"text","text":") with [shooting] stars. (TA.) [In the MA, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajuwmN","text_ar":"رَجُومٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", as well as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajiymN","text_ar":"رَجِيمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", is explained as signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Stoned:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but it is probably a mistranscription for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marojuwmN","text_ar":"مَرْجُومٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1049},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Slain"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in any manner,"},{"kind":"text","text":"but generally meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"put to death by being stoned"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"latakuwnan~a mina","text_ar":"لَتَكُونَنَّ مِنَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almarojuwmiyna","text_ar":"المَرْجُومِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [xxvi. 116], is explained as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou shalt assuredly be of those slain in the most evil manner of slaughter:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or the meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of those smitten with stones:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reviled."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd, Jel.) ―         -b3-  Also the former, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Cursed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"accursed;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in this sense, i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAll~aEonapi","text_ar":"بِاللَّعْنَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marojuwmN","text_ar":"مَرْجُومٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", applied to the devil. (TA.) ―         -b4-  And (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Reviled;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marojuwmN","text_ar":"مَرْجُومٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", as shown above;] and in this sense, also, said to be applied to the devil: and so in the two senses here following. (TA.) ―         -b5-  (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Driven away; expelled; put,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"placed, at a distance, away,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"far away."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b6-  And (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Cut off from friendly"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"loving communion"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intercourse; forsaken;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abandoned."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["TA"]}]}}